Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urbecka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rbecka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/9/01 3:21:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.dmcom.net/obrien/rbecka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Good Post on Raid Discipline</span><hr size=1> It *should* be required reading. Unfortunately there is no way to enforce this. Like so many have said -- if you can not wait at the end of a raid for whatever is gonna be distributed, (lotto, etc) don't come. We all have to wait the same amount of time.. and nobody's schedule is any more important than anyone else's. Sit there and behave, or get up and leave. Above all, keep the comments regarding speed of what is happening to yourself. (or your group, if your leader will tolerate it) That was the only beef I had regarding the Vox raid -- damn people. Be quiet when somethin's being done. Who knows.. next raid it could be your body in the bear pit.<br>
